19 There is included in the appropriation to this program $30,000 from
20 the General Fund for FY2025-26 for the purpose of contracting for
21 services with an organization with the primary goal of ensuring
22 sustainability in juvenile justice reform. Such contract shall be used to
23 explore making probation, the district and state court systems, law
24 enforcement, county attorneys, public defenders, and school districts
25 more effective partners in juvenile justice reform. Any required funding
26 greater than the amount provided in the contract shall be acquired from
27 other sources prior to entering into a contract for services with the
28 organization. The contract shall include requirements that the
29 organization work with a county having a population of one hundred fifty
30 thousand or more inhabitants willing to lease or grant county-owned
31 property for the purpose of creating a facility to address juvenile
-17-

